        <div class="content-body">
          <p>Getting accepted to a university abroad is a major achievement, but the transition to a new country, culture, and academic system brings its own set of challenges. Grant Consulting's pre-departure training program prepares students for every aspect of life abroad so they can arrive confident, informed, and ready to succeed from day one. Our sessions are led by advisors who have firsthand experience living and studying in the countries our students are heading to.</p>
          <p>Cultural orientation is a key part of our training. We cover the social norms, communication styles, and everyday customs of your destination country so you know what to expect and how to navigate new situations comfortably. From understanding classroom etiquette and professor-student relationships to managing daily tasks like banking, transportation, and healthcare, we make sure nothing catches you off guard.</p>
          <p>Academic preparation and practical life skills round out the program. We help students understand the expectations of their new academic environment — including grading systems, research standards, and time management techniques — and cover essential topics like budgeting, cooking basics, accommodation setup, and staying connected with family back home. Our goal is to make sure you are not just academically prepared but genuinely ready to thrive in your new surroundings.</p>
        </div>

